<h2>Virtuoso's in Schools</h2>
<p>Learning to play an instrument can aid a person's mental and emotional growth. It is an opportunity for people to expand their extra-cirricular skills and involve themselves in the magical art form that is music. It is an entertaining, advantageous and rewarding experience.</p>
<p>Beginning this journey at a young age will definitely be of great use to whoever takes it up. </p>

<p>At Virtuoso's we are committed to guiding people through the wonderful world of music, and ready to offer our services to your student <span class=bigger>at your school.</span></p>

<h2>Our Offering</h2>

<ul>
	
	<li><p>Well-trained and qualified music teachers are provided by VPSM to execute the program; which removes any Human Resource related issues for the school.</p></li>
	
	<li><p>All infrastructure including pianos, guitars, etc. are provided by VPSM without any cost to the school. Each child has access to his own individual instrument during class.</p></li>

	<li><p>The progress of each child is tracked and assessed; and the same is communicated to the school management and parents on a periodic basis.</p></li>

	<li><p>We strive to create a thriving musical environment in schoolsÂ designed to be fun & engaging with use of audio-visual resources in classrooms.</p></li>

	<li><p>We provide children the opportunity to perform via annual recitals.</p></li>

	<li><p>We organise live performances by  artistes to give exposure and motivation to the students.</p></li>

	<li><p>We provide regular updates to the parent community on music & education.</p></li>

	<li><p>Instrument Specialisation (which includes guitar and keyboards)</p></li>

	<li><p>Theory of Music</p></li>

	<li><p>Based on the interest and inclination of the students we also prepare students for globally accredited examination boards including Trinity College, London.</p></li>

</ul>

<h2>Curriculum</h2>

<p>
At VPSM we follow performance based curriculum focusing on instrument learning skills using internationally acclaimed methodology. This gives students of all ages the opportunity to learn in a classroom environment Keyboard performance skills and music theory. Students will be given the opportunity to progress further by taking performance examinations, individual instrumental lessons and participate in recitals. Instrument specialization in Keyboard & Guitar.
</p>

<br>
<p>Contact us so we can work out an arrangement for us to teach at your school.</p>
